      "content": "Minimum wage hikes can be a double-edged sword for small businesses. On one hand, they can lead to increased consumer spending as workers have more disposable income. On the other hand, they can also raise operational costs, potentially squeezing profit margins. In a small town with a low cost of living, the impact might be more pronounced, as businesses may struggle to absorb the increased labor costs without raising prices or cutting back on staff. It's crucial to weigh the benefits of higher wages against the financial strain they might impose on your business.",
