      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, it feels like a losing battle for the little guy sometimes. honestly, it feels a bit like these policies are designed by people in big cities who have no clue how a small town economy actually works. do you think there's any real validity to the idea that these mandates are just a way to force small businesses out so big chains can take over?",
